The paper presents a randomized partitioning procedure for graph coloring in distributed and parallel computing models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to distributed computing (cs.DC), graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DS), data structures and algorithms (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG) which often involves parallel and distributed computing. Among these, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the paper's focus on distributed graph coloring algorithms.
